[{"id":"VR914704","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In each of two experiments, light is incident on a narrow slit and forms a diffraction pattern on a screen located some distance from the slit. The screens in the two experiments are the same distance from the respective slits, and the two diffraction patterns have brightness minima at the same positions with respect to the central bright maximum. In Experiment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, the incident light has frequency <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f sub 1\"><math alttext=\"f sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and the width of the slit is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. In Experiment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the incident light has frequency <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 f sub 1\"><math alttext=\"2 f sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. What is the width of the slit in Experiment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR914704_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"one half a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"ma